23- Not sure how to answer something so abstract.

Connecting with others, I guess is a decent way of simplifying it?
I'm bad at communicating verbally, and I suck at reading as well, so art is a good way for me to connect with others and explain/show what I like or feel.

22- I love ballpoint and gel pens, adding highlighter or alcohol markers and sometimes pencil to them.
My other fave thing is acrylic painting and gouache, despite not showing them much here!

21- Clip Studio Paint, my beloved.

(Procreate as well, but CSP is the love of my life my wife my wiwwwfie mym wifie)
20- I need music blasting at stupid high volume (bad hearing, so it's justified shut up!!!!!!!!!!) or else I will become a dissociating slug

19- Inspired! 

I love seeing different styles and skill levels of art all around, it makes me so happy seeing so so so much variety and so many different ways to interpret/execute pieces!!! Makes me think a lot out of my little box and try and experiment even more!
18- Bro I draw at stupidly high speeds, if anything I'm posting way too fucking much lmao
17- I do it constantly, if I didn't I wouldn't learn anything new nor improve on what I already know!
16- Eyes, hands, shoes, ti🅱🅱ies, plants.
15- Points at n 6
14- Need to loosen up the postures, I make characters a bit too stiff still sometimes, as well as proportions and style polishing. Never enough improvement on those.
13- I now draw x50 times more than I used to. I do at least 2 pieces and one painting a day, whether they're posted or not, as well as 2h of warmups worth of doodles.

12- "Average piece"? Not sure what that'd mean for me.

For colored sketches anywhere between  20min and 1h. For flats, if I don't have to send any WIPs, About 2h if the piece isn't too complex.
11- 4 years ago, on a now forever gone sketchbook. https://t.co/g1Zy3G4XfN

10- I've done collabs only once that I can remember? (I have shit memory please forgive me if I forgor)

It was with Ase ( @ / softtummybitch ) ages ago (spoiler it was really cute and cosy).

I don't do them unless I'm really close to the artist!! Anxiety brain!!

9- There's place for both. 

I do a TON of canvas painting, but I don't post it online because I don't feel like it. It doesn't fit this account, it's personal, and it's staying that way.

Likewise, I do a TON of work for others and post it online and love the interactions!!
8- Not confident about everything, no! I have lots to learn and improve on yet, tons of growing and experimenting left!!! Some pieces I AM confident about, but can't be confident about them all lol

7- I'm a freelancer so this is technically professional!! 
I try to still look at it from a hobby perspective though, to not sap all the joy from it.

6- Complex angles, man. I have really bad eyesight and therefore some really shitty depth perception, so trying to adapt a 3D thing I can barely perceive correctly to 2D is hell sometimes!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
5- I use references all the time. Sorry, artists are not computers with infinite knowledge about every single item, pose, style and feel.

4- A variety of things....

· Girls
· Animals
· Fashion, clothing/accessories in general
· Plants
· Repeating patterns
· Teeth and claws
3- The only drawing classes I've taken are in tech drawing, for my engineering career 💀

2- I started painting and doodling about 25 years ago LMAO

But if we mean drawing "with a purpose", as in actively aiming to improve and portray feelings or ideas as accurately as possible...that'd be 15 years!

1- This is HARD, honestly. I love both, and they feel equally rewarding to me!
I'd say it depends mostly on my mood and how bad my hand trembles are. The worse the trembling is, the less I enjoy traditional (for obvious reasons haha). The worse my mood, the less I enjoy digital!
